name: De' Routes TOWN CAFE

reviews.text:
Food is delicious. Tried the Gambas Al Ajillo,  Bangers and Mash, Quesadilas and Mutton varuval. All are sooo...Good.
Excellent service. Staff are friendly and chef will come out to make sure food is up to customer's standards.
Atmosphere is great. Very chill.
Love this place. This is our 4th time here. Will definitely come back many more times.

It's a nice corner bar for relaxation at night. We had the carbonara and ribeye steak. Carbonara was great, so creamy and pasta was al dente. Chef was really nice, he personally came out to take the order and mentioned that he can cook the medium rare steak a little more if we decide we prefer it a little more cooked. But the steak was good, just üëçWe also had the red velvet cake after the meal which was dense and filling. Will be nice if theres some music playing at night to add to the atmosphere. Otherwise it's just the sound of chatter from customers from the other tables.
Had a quick staycation near this cafe, food was served hot, very delicious and service was great.
The Food Was So Delicious And The Staff Were So Friendly Overall  Experience Was Great Will Come Again Soon
The pasta and quesadillas were absolutely delightful. The waitresses were very kind.
